ges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Maelog was born about 1170, in Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales. He married verch Gruffudd ap Ifor Bach about 1195, in Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1170–":"umbes 1170–Surnud","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1203–1234":"1203–1234","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","about 1195":"umbes 1195","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1175":"1175","1170":"1170","Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"about 1170–":"noin 1170–Kuollut","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1203–1234":"1203–1234","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","about 1195":"noin 1195","about 1170":"noin 1170","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1175":"1175","1170":"1170","Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"about 1170–":"environ 1170–Décédé","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1203–1234":"1203–1234","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","about 1195":"environ 1195","about 1170":"environ 1170","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1175":"1175","1170":"1170","Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Newport, Monmouthshire, Galles","Wales":"Galles","lifeSummary":"Sir William Maelog est né environ 1170, à Newport, Monmouthshire, Galles. Il a épousé verch Gruffudd ap Ifor Bach environ 1195, à Galles. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1170–":"um 117